Question: Find the Runner-Up Score

Given the participants' scores in a competition, find the runner-up score. The runner-up score is the second highest distinct score.

Input Format
The first line contains an integer n, the number of scores.
The second line contains n space-separated integers representing the scores.
Constraints
2 ≤ n ≤ 10
Scores can be positive or negative integers.

> Solution:

if __name__ == '__main__':
    n = int(input())
    arr = list(map(int, input().split()))
    
    ar = list(set(arr))
    
    ar.sort(reverse=True)
        
        
    print(ar[1])
